   "source": [
    "<html>\n",
    "<p style=\"font-size:32px\"><strong>Final Project, Part 2: Post-training with Reinforcement Fine-tuning</strong></p>\n",
    "</html>\n",
    "\n",
    "# Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "In this project, I will fine-tune a pre-trained language model (`HuggingFaceTB/SmolLM2-135M-Instruct`) to teach it how to use a Quant Library—specifically, a Black-Scholes option pricing calculator. The goal is to create a model that learns when to call tools and how to format those calls correctly.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Project Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "I follow the standard Reinforcement Fine-Tuning (RFT) pipeline:\n",
    "1. **Data Preparation**: Create synthetic training/validation data with tool calls\n",
    "2. **Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT)**: Train the model to produce tool calls in the correct format\n",
    "3. **Reward Function Design**: Define what makes a good tool call\n",
    "4. **GRPO Training**: Use reinforcement learning to optimize tool-use behavior\n",
    "5. **Evaluation**: Measure performance on held-out examples\n",
    "\n",
    "## Tool Specification\n",
    "\n",
    "The Black-Scholes option pricing function has the signature:\n",
    "```\n",
    "def bs(S: float, K: float, T: float, r: float, sigma: float, type: str) -> float\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "When the model wants to call this, it outputs:\n",
    "```\n",
    "<tool_code>bs(S=100, K=110, T=.5, r=5.1/100, sigma=16/100, type=\"call\")</tool_code>\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Section 1: Setup & Configuration\n",
    "\n",
    "First, I'll set up the environment, import necessary libraries, and lock in HuggingFace versions to ensure reproducibility."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import random\n",
    "import re\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "from typing import Dict, List, Tuple, Optional\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# HuggingFace imports with version checking\n",
    "from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer, TrainingArguments\n",
    "from trl import SFTConfig, SFTTrainer\n",
    "from datasets import Dataset, DatasetDict\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set random seeds for reproducibility\n",
    "torch.manual_seed(42)\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('='*70)\n",
    "print('ENVIRONMENT & VERSION CHECK')\n",
    "print('='*70)\n",
    "print(f'PyTorch version: {torch.__version__}')\n",
    "print(f'Device: {torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Version lock for stability\n",
    "import transformers\n",
    "print(f'Transformers version: {transformers.__version__}')\n",
    "print(f'✓ Environment ready')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Section 2: Data Generation\n",
    "\n",
    "I create synthetic training data where:  \n",
    "- **Positive examples**: Prompts that SHOULD trigger tool calls, with correct Black-Scholes calls\n",
    "- **Negative examples**: Prompts that should NOT trigger tool calls (general questions)\n",
    "\n",
    "The data is designed to teach the model the conditional logic: \"When to call tools and when not to.\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def generate_training_data(n_tool_calls: int = 50, n_non_tool: int = 30):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n    
    "    Generate synthetic SFT training data for tool use.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    data = []\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Option pricing parameters (realistic ranges)\n",
    "    spot_prices = [80, 90, 100, 110, 120]\n",
    "    strikes = [85, 95, 105, 115, 125]\n",
    "    times_to_expiry = [0.25, 0.5, 1.0]  # 3m, 6m, 1y\n",
    "    rates = [0.02, 0.03, 0.05]  # 2%, 3%, 5%\n",
    "    vols = [0.15, 0.20, 0.25]  # 15%, 20%, 25%\n",
    "    option_types = ['call', 'put']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # ===== POSITIVE EXAMPLES: Prompts that should call Black-Scholes =====\n",
    "    for i in range(n_tool_calls):\n",
    "        S = np.random.choice(spot_prices)\n",
    "        K = np.random.choice(strikes)\n",
    "        T = np.random.choice(times_to_expiry)\n",
    "        r = np.random.choice(rates) / 100  # Convert to decimal\n",
    "        sigma = np.random.choice(vols) / 100\n",
    "        opt_type = np.random.choice(option_types)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Varied prompt styles to increase diversity\n",
    "        prompt_styles = [\n",
    "            f\"What is the price of a {opt_type} option with spot={S}, strike={K}, time={T}y, rate={r*100}%, volatility={sigma*100}%?\",\n",
    "            f\"Calculate the Black-Scholes value: S={S}, K={K}, T={T}, r={r}, sigma={sigma}, type={opt_type}\",\n",
    "            f\"Price this {opt_type} option: underlying={S}, strike={K}, expiry={T}y, rf_rate={r*100}%, vol={sigma*100}%\",\n",
    "            f\"Using Black-Scholes: {opt_type} option, spot {S}, strike {K}, {T} years, {r*100}% rate, {sigma*100}% vol\",\n",
    "        ]\n",
    "        prompt = np.random.choice(prompt_styles)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Format the tool call response\n",
    "        response = f\"<tool_code>bs(S={S}, K={K}, T={T}, r={r}, sigma={sigma}, type=\\\"{opt_type}\\\")</tool_code>\"\n",
    "        \n",
    "        data.append({'prompt': prompt, 'response': response, 'tool_call': True})\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # ===== NEGATIVE EXAMPLES: Prompts that should NOT call tools =====\n",
    "    general_prompts = [\n",
    "        'What is a call option?',\n",
    "        'Explain the difference between calls and puts.',\n",
    "        'What does volatility mean in finance?',\n",
    "        'How does the risk-free rate affect options?',\n",
    "        'What is implied volatility?',\n",
    "        'Explain the Greeks in option pricing.',\n",
    "        'What is the time value of an option?',\n",
    "        'How do dividends affect option pricing?',\n",
    "        'What is put-call parity?',\n",
    "        'Explain early exercise in American options.',\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    general_responses = [\n",
    "        'A call option gives the holder the right to buy an underlying asset at a fixed strike price.',\n",
    "        'Calls give the right to buy; puts give the right to sell.',\n",
    "        'Volatility measures how much an asset\'s price fluctuates.',\n",
    "        'Higher risk-free rates typically increase call values and decrease put values.',\n",
    "        'Implied volatility is the market\'s expectation of future volatility.',\n",
    "        'The Greeks are Delta, Gamma, Vega, Theta, and Rho.',\n",
    "        'Time value is the premium above intrinsic value.',\n",
    "        'Dividends reduce call values and increase put values.',\n",
    "        'Put-call parity is a relationship between put and call prices.',\n",
    "        'American options can be exercised early; European cannot.',\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(n_non_tool):\n",
    "        idx = i % len(general_prompts)\n",
    "        data.append({\n",
    "            'prompt': general_prompts[idx],\n",
    "            'response': general_responses[idx],\n",
    "            'tool_call': False\n",
    "        })\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Generating training data...')\n",
    "train_data = generate_training_data(n_tool_calls=50, n_non_tool=30)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'✓ Generated {len(train_data)} training examples')\n",
    "print(f'  - Tool calls: {train_data[\"tool_call\"].sum()}')\n",
    "print(f'  - Non-tool: {(~train_data[\"tool_call\"]).sum()}')\n",
    "print(f'\\nSample training example:')\n",
    "sample_idx = train_data[train_data['tool_call']].index[0]\n",
    "print(f\"Prompt: {train_data.loc[sample_idx, 'prompt']}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Response: {train_data.loc[sample_idx, 'response']}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create train/val split\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "train_df, val_df = train_test_split(train_data, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=train_data['tool_call'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Train/Val split:')\n",
    "print(f'  Train: {len(train_df)} examples')\n",
    "print(f'  Val: {len(val_df)} examples')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert to HF Dataset format\n",
    "train_ds = Dataset.from_pandas(train_df[['prompt', 'response']])\n",
    "val_ds = Dataset.from_pandas(val_df[['prompt', 'response']])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'✓ Datasets converted to HuggingFace format')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Section 3: Model Loading & SFT Training\n",
    "\n",
    "I load the base model and tokenizer, then perform Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT) on the tool-use data. This teaches the model the basic format and when to call tools."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "MODEL_NAME = 'HuggingFaceTB/SmolLM2-135M-Instruct'\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Loading model and tokenizer...')\n",
    "model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\n",
    "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\n",
    "\n",
    "if tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n",
    "    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'✓ Model loaded: {MODEL_NAME}')\n",
    "print(f'  Parameters: {sum(p.numel() for p in model.parameters()) / 1e6:.1f}M')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Formatting function for SFT\n",
    "def formatting_func(examples):\n",
    "    texts = []\n",
    "    for prompt, response in zip(examples['prompt'], examples['response']):\n",
    "        text = f\"{prompt}\\n{response}\"\n",
    "        texts.append(text)\n",
    "    return {\"text\": texts}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Format datasets\n",
    "train_ds_formatted = train_ds.map(formatting_func, batched=True).select_columns(['text'])\n",
    "val_ds_formatted = val_ds.map(formatting_func, batched=True).select_columns(['text'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'✓ Datasets formatted for SFT training')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# SFT Configuration\n",
    "print('\\n' + '='*70)\n",
    "print('PHASE 1: SUPERVISED FINE-TUNING (SFT)')\n",
    "print('='*70)\n",
    "\n",
    "SFT_MAX_STEPS = 100\n",
    "SFT_BATCH_SIZE = 8\n",
    "SFT_GRAD_ACCUM = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'SFT Configuration:')\n",
    "print(f'  Max steps: {SFT_MAX_STEPS}')\n",
    "print(f'  Batch size: {SFT_BATCH_SIZE}')\n",
    "print(f'  Learning rate: 2e-5')\n",
    "print(f'  Warmup steps: 5')\n",
    "\n",
    "sft_config = SFTConfig(\n",
    "    output_dir='./sft_checkpoint',\n",
    "    num_train_epochs=1,\n",
    "    max_steps=SFT_MAX_STEPS,\n",
    "    per_device_train_batch_size=SFT_BATCH_SIZE,\n",
    "    gradient_accumulation_steps=SFT_GRAD_ACCUM,\n",
    "    logging_steps=10,\n",
    "    learning_rate=2e-5,\n",
    "    max_grad_norm=1.0,\n",
    "    fp16=torch.cuda.is_available(),\n",
    "    lr_scheduler_type='linear',\n",
    "    warmup_steps=5,\n",
    "    save_strategy='steps',\n",
    "    save_steps=20,\n",
    "    eval_strategy='steps',\n",
    "    eval_steps=20,\n",
    "    seed=42,\n",
    "    report_to=[],\n",
    "    max_seq_length=512,\n",
    "    dataset_text_field='text',\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "sft_trainer = SFTTrainer(\n",
    "    model=model,\n",
    "    args=sft_config,\n",
    "    train_dataset=train_ds_formatted,\n",
    "    eval_dataset=val_ds_formatted,\n",
    "    tokenizer=tokenizer,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Starting SFT training...')\n",
    "sft_result = sft_trainer.train()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'✓ SFT training complete')\n",
    "print(f'  Final training loss: {sft_result.training_loss:.4f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save SFT model\n",
    "sft_model_path = './sft_model'\n",
    "sft_trainer.model.save_pretrained(sft_model_path)\n",
    "tokenizer.save_pretrained(sft_model_path)\n",
    "print(f'✓ SFT model saved to: {sft_model_path}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Section 4: Reward Function\n",
    "\n",
    "The reward function evaluates how good a model's response is. I design it to reward:\n",
    "1. **Presence of tool call**: Does the response contain `<tool_code>...</tool_code>`?\n",
    "2. **Correct format**: Does the tool call match the Black-Scholes signature?\n",
    "3. **Appropriateness**: Is the tool call used when appropriate?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def compute_reward(prompt: str, response: str, should_use_tool: bool = True) -> float:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Compute reward for a model response.\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns: float in [0, 1]\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    reward = 0.0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Check if response contains tool call markers\n",
    "    has_tool_markers = '<tool_code>' in response and '</tool_code>' in response\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if not has_tool_markers:\n",
    "        # If tool should NOT be used, no markers is correct\n",
    "        if not should_use_tool:\n",
    "            return 0.8  # Good: didn't use tool when shouldn't\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return 0.1  # Bad: didn't use tool when should\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Has tool markers - extract and validate\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        start_idx = response.find('<tool_code>') + len('<tool_code>')\n",
    "        end_idx = response.find('</tool_code>')\n",
    "        tool_call = response[start_idx:end_idx].strip()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Check if it looks like a Black-Scholes call\n",
    "        if 'bs(' in tool_call:\n",
    "            # Try to validate the format\n",
    "            required_params = ['S=', 'K=', 'T=', 'r=', 'sigma=', 'type=']\n",
    "            has_all_params = all(param in tool_call for param in required_params)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            if has_all_params:\n",
    "                # Excellent: correct tool, correct format\n",
    "                if should_use_tool:\n",
    "                    return 0.95  # Perfect\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    return 0.1   # Used tool when shouldn't\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                # Good try but missing parameters\n",
    "                return 0.5\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            # Tool call but not Black-Scholes\n",
    "            return 0.3\n",
    "    except:\n",
    "        # Parsing error\n",
    "        return 0.2\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test reward function\n",
    "test_cases = [\n",
    "    ('What is a call?', 'A call is an option to buy.', False, 0.8),\n",
    "    ('Price S=100, K=110, T=0.5, r=0.051, sigma=0.16, type=call', '<tool_code>bs(S=100, K=110, T=0.5, r=0.051, sigma=0.16, type=\"call\")</tool_code>', True, 0.95),\n",
    "    ('Price an option', 'Let me call the tool: <tool_code>bs(S=100, K=110)</tool_code>', True, 0.5),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Reward function test cases:')\n",
    "for prompt, response, should_use, expected in test_cases:\n",
    "    r = compute_reward(prompt, response, should_use)\n",
    "    print(f'  Reward: {r:.2f} (expected ~{expected:.2f})')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Section 5: Evaluation on SFT Model\n",
    "\n",
    "Before moving to GRPO, I evaluate the SFT-trained model to see if it has learned the basic tool-use patterns."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('\\n' + '='*70)\n",
    "print('SFT MODEL EVALUATION')\n",
    "print('='*70)\n",
    "\n",
    "sft_model_eval = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(sft_model_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "rewards_sft = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for idx, row in val_df.iterrows():\n",
    "    prompt = row['prompt']\n",
    "    tool_call = row['tool_call']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    inputs = tokenizer(prompt, return_tensors='pt', truncation=True, max_length=256)\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        outputs = sft_model_eval.generate(\n",
    "            inputs['input_ids'],\n",
    "            max_length=200,\n",
    "            num_return_sequences=1,\n",
    "            temperature=0.7,\n",
    "            do_sample=True,\n",
    "            pad_token_id=tokenizer.eos_token_id,\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    generated = tokenizer.decode(outputs[0], skip_special_tokens=True)\n",
    "    reward = compute_reward(prompt, generated, should_use_tool=tool_call)\n",
    "    rewards_sft.append(reward)\n",
    "\n",
    "avg_reward = np.mean(rewards_sft)\n",
    "std_reward = np.std(rewards_sft)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'SFT Model Performance:')\n",
    "print(f'  Average reward: {avg_reward:.3f} ± {std_reward:.3f}')\n",
    "print(f'  Min/Max: {np.min(rewards_sft):.3f} / {np.max(rewards_sft):.3f}')\n",
    "print(f'  Median: {np.median(rewards_sft):.3f}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show example\n",
    "example_idx = val_df[val_df['tool_call']].index[0]\n",
    "example_prompt = val_df.loc[example_idx, 'prompt']\n",
    "inputs = tokenizer(example_prompt, return_tensors='pt', truncation=True)\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    outputs = sft_model_eval.generate(inputs['input_ids'], max_length=200)\n",
    "example_response = tokenizer.decode(outputs[0], skip_special_tokens=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'\\nExample output:')\n",
    "print(f'  Prompt: {example_prompt}')\n",
    "print(f'  Response: {example_response}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Section 6: GRPO Training (if available)\n",
    "\n",
    "Now I attempt to use GRPO (Group Relative Policy Optimization) to further improve the model using the reward function as guidance.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note:** GRPO may not be available in all HuggingFace TRL versions. If unavailable, the SFT model serves as the final checkpoint."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Check if GRPOTrainer is available\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    from trl import GRPOTrainer, GRPOConfig\n",
    "    GRPO_AVAILABLE = True\n",
    "    print('✓ GRPOTrainer available')\n",
    "except ImportError:\n",
    "    GRPO_AVAILABLE = False\n",
    "    print('⚠ GRPOTrainer not available - will use SFT model as final checkpoint')\n",
    "    print('  Reason: May depend on newer TRL version or optional dependencies')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if GRPO_AVAILABLE:\n",
    "    print('\\n' + '='*70)\n",
    "    print('PHASE 2: GRPO REINFORCEMENT LEARNING')\n",
    "    print('='*70)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Prepare prompts only (for generation)\n",
    "    train_prompts_ds = Dataset.from_pandas(train_df[['prompt']])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Define reward function for GRPO\n",
    "    def reward_fn(prompts, completions):\n",
    "        rewards = []\n",
    "        for prompt, completion in zip(prompts, completions):\n",
    "            r = compute_reward(prompt, completion, should_use_tool=True)\n",
    "            rewards.append(r)\n",
    "        return rewards\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # GRPO Configuration\n",
    "    grpo_config = GRPOConfig(\n",
    "        output_dir='./grpo_checkpoint',\n",
    "        learning_rate=1e-5,\n",
    "        per_device_train_batch_size=4,\n",
    "        gradient_accumulation_steps=1,\n",
    "        num_train_epochs=3,\n",
    "        num_generations=4,  # Generate 4 outputs per prompt\n",
    "        beta=0.01,  # KL penalty weight\n",
    "        log_level='info',\n",
    "        logging_steps=5,\n",
    "        save_steps=10,\n",
    "        seed=42,\n",
    "        report_to=[],\n",
    "        max_prompt_length=256,\n",
    "        max_completion_length=150,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f'GRPO Configuration:')\n",
    "    print(f'  Learning rate: 1e-5')\n",
    "    print(f'  Beta (KL penalty): 0.01')\n",
    "    print(f'  Generations per prompt: 4')\n",
    "    print(f'  Epochs: 3')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Create GRPO trainer\n",
